content: I've bought several of the Dr Seuss apps for my daughter to use. Tried to use them on a plane journey, but because of the lack of internet connection none of them worked. Why does the licence need to be checked if I've already paid for it? This needs to get sorted as we travel often and she was very dissapointed
replyContent: I would suggest you delete the app and reinstall it. First uninstall the app from your device. Go to Google Play on your device and select Apps. Tap the down arrow with the line under it at the top of the screen. Locate the app that you would like reinstalled select it. The app now only checks for the license once when the app is downloaded.
